  "prompt": "What are good examples of websites built using Adobe ColdFusion?",
  "response": "Adobe ColdFusion is a web application development platform that is often used to build dynamic websites and applications. While many businesses use ColdFusion behind the scenes, it may not always be obvious which sites are built on this platform since the technology is not usually visible to end-users. However, here are some notable examples of websites and applications that have historically been built using Adobe ColdFusion:\n\n1. **BBC**: The British Broadcasting Corporation has used ColdFusion for some of its web applications.\n  \n2. **Coca-Cola**: They have used ColdFusion for various internal applications and possibly portions of their web presence.\n\n3. **McDonald's**: Some of their internal systems and possibly public-facing pages have utilized ColdFusion.\n\n4. **United States Federal Government**: Various agencies have historically used ColdFusion for some of their web applications and services.\n\n5. **Fidelity Investments**: Parts of their financial services platform were built using ColdFusion.\n\n6. **eBay**: Some of their earlier web applications were reported to have been built using ColdFusion.\n\n7. **Deloitte**: The consulting firm has leveraged ColdFusion for client-related projects.\n\n8. **A variety of educational institutions**: Many universities and schools have used ColdFusion for their content management systems and internal applications.\n\nWhile the technology may not be as prevalent in newer projects as it once was, ColdFusion still has a loyal user base, particularly in sectors where rapid application development and ease of use are paramount. If you're interested in a specific industry or application type, you might find additional examples that align closely with your interests.",
